      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Sure, here's a rough itinerary to help you plan your trip to Tokyo.\n\n**Day 1:** Arrive in Tokyo and check into your hotel in Marunouchi. After settling in, you can visit the nearby Ginza district for some shopping if you have the time.\n\n**Day 2:** \n- Morning: Attend your first meeting in Marunouchi. \n- Afternoon: Take the Tokyo Metro to Shibuya via the Marunouchi Station. Try Uminonakamichi Street, near Shibuya Station for a quieter café area where you can get work done.\n- Evening: Return to Marunouchi for the night, or explore the night-life of the district if needed.\n\n**Day 3:**\n- Morning: Attend your final meeting in Shibuya.\n- Afternoon: Spend time downtown Shibuya. You may want to visit the Hachiko Statue nearby, which is a popular meeting spot.\n- Evening: Back in Marunouchi area, you can relax into the evening or complete any required work.\n\n**Day 4:**\n- Morning: Check out of your hotel in Marunouchi and head to Shibuya. Spend some leisure time in the district exploring shops and attractions.\n- Afternoon: For",
